description.p:
a) Cat is at least one cationic species;


b) M is at least one species of metallic element;


c) X is at least one species selected from the group consisting of VO4, SO4, Cl, Br, I, H2 O, HCOO and NO2 ;


d) E is at least one species selected from the group consisting of H2 O, N2 H4 and organic solvents;


e) L is at least one species selected from the group consisting of H2 O, O, NO, N2, acetyl acetone, pyridine, 2,2'-bipyridine, (H2 N(CH2)d NH2) (d=2 or 3), RNH2 and R2 NH;


where if L=monodentate, then z=4 and where if L=bidentate, then z=2 or 4; and


a=2 or 3;


m=the number of cations and is in the range of about 0 to about 12;


n=the units of negative charge and is in the range of about 2 to about 6, except where m=0 in which case n=0 and


b=the number of solvent/neutral molecule(s)--E, in the lattice and is in the range of about 12 to about 30.

